                Lobbyists who can point to specific wins—"I passed HB 2847," "I killed the regulatory change targeting your industry"—command premium pricing.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-3">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>Documentation matters:</strong> Keep detailed records of your successes. Case studies sell future clients.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border border-border p-6">
              <h4 class="font-bold text-orange-900 mb-2">Leadership Relationships</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-3">
                Strong connections with Speaker, Lt. Governor, committee chairs, and their senior staff make you significantly more valuable to clients with high-stakes issues.
              </p>
              <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-3">
                <p class="text-xs"><strong>The premium:</strong> Former legislators and senior staff command 2-3x rates of equally skilled "outside" lobbyists for this reason.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
