            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-amber-900 mb-3">What First-Year Income Looks Like</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 mb-3">
              Your first year as an independent lobbyist will probably be a financial struggle. Most new lobbyists earn $30K-$60K their first year while building their practice. Some earn nothing and supplement with consulting work.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-amber-900 font-bold">
              Don't expect six figures immediately. But if you stick with it, build reputation, and deliver results, the earning potential by year 5-7 is substantial. This is a long-term play, not a get-rich-quick scheme.
            </p>
